<div class="box">
	<h4>Options</h4>
	<p>
		Options are runtime configurations of an application, it can be
		really useful to turn certain features on or off within the 
		application. Engine comes with a few predefined options that 
		should not be deleted.
	</p>
	<p>
		Options are categorized by default, this can be useful for large 
		applications that needs many runtime options. Whether options are 
		split into core categories or per application namespace doesn't play 
		a role, as categories programmically is just visual candy.
	</p>

